  "elapsed_s": 10.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "These identity cards were-- had been distributed in 1940 already.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And any Jewish holder of that identity card got a-- a stamp, a big, black J.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] These identity cards entitled the holder to obtain a distribution-- food distribution card.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we had to-- a little coupons.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And for each food-- item of food or textile that you purchased, coupons had to be put in.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Once you had exhausted your coupons, you had to wait until the next month that you got new coupons.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Like most Western European countries, Holland had a system of central register offices.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "That means that every child, every inhabitant of a city or town or village, had to be registered in this central office in a-- in a system that showed the card, date of birth, address, and religion.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And that fact, that the religion was shown on these cards, on this registry, contributed to the catastrophe that befell the Jews in Holland and in other European countries, because when the Germans invaded Holland, one of the first things they did was to occupy immediately the, what is called in Holland, the [DUTCH], in German, in Germany, [GERMAN], and take a hold of all these data, which enabled them to later get the Jews together.",
      "word_count": 76
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] 1941 started, as I said, with a lot of new decrees.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
